OL,6,FIn reply, Eluned Morgan said that, "I
OL,7,Fjust think we've got to be very
OL,8,Fserious about this, because this is an
OL,9,Fissue that's causing concern to a lot
OL,10,Fof people in Wales. As you know,
OL,11,Fbenefit reform is not devolved to
OL,12,FWales, but Welsh Labour will always be
OL,13,Fthe party that wants to encourage and
OL,14,Fto support people back into work. We
OL,15,Fare the Labour Party, and we're not
OL,16,Fgoing to apologise for that."
