OL,6,F"But on the other hand, it is
OL,7,Fimportant that we have fairness in the
OL,8,Fsystem and that we protect the most
OL,9,Fvulnerable on every occasion. We have
OL,10,Fmade the case very clearly to the
OL,11,FSecretary of State responsible in
OL,12,Fterms of the impact that we think it
OL,13,Fwill have on people in Wales; we have
OL,14,Furged her to consider the case we have
OL,15,Fmade, and obviously it will be up to
OL,16,Fthe MPs to determine how they vote."
OL,18,FThe Prime Minister, meanwhile, has
OL,19,Ftold UK Cabinet ministers that the
