OL,6,FSir Keir Starmer himself later told
OL,7,Freporters that he would not pause the
OL,8,Freforms. He said that "We were elected
OL,9,Fin to change what is broken in our
OL,10,Fcountry. The welfare system is broken,
OL,11,Fand that's why we will press ahead
OL,12,Fwith our reforms."
OL,14,F"It's very important that we do so,
OL,15,Fbecause the current system is not
OL,16,Fworking for anybody. People are
OL,17,Ftrapped in it, and I'm not prepared to
OL,18,Fallow that to happen. So we will press
OL,19,Fforward with our reforms."
